SANTA CRUZ PORTLAND CEMENT COMPANY, Petitioner, v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Respondent. No. 8382. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit Nov. 8, 1937. George E. H. Goodner, of. Washington, D. C., for petitioner. James W. Morris, Asst. Atty. Gen., for respondent.

Before DENMAN, STEPHENS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered petition to review in above cause dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and mandate of this court issue forthwith.
